Title: A superficial esophageal cancer with a diverticulum cured by endoscopic submucosal dissection.
Abstract: Esophageal diverticulum are rare. However, Esophageal cancer that involves diverticula is relatively rare. Here we reported a rare case of a superficial esophageal cancer with an esophageal diverticulum, which was invisible before the endoscopic submucosal dissection. The cancer was successfully removed by ESD with no perforation.
