Abstract: In the present study, a rare familial case of severe thalassemia with compound spontaneous mutations is reported. A 2.5閳ユ啅ear閳ユ唭ld boy, who suffered from severe anemia with yellowish skin, enlarged liver and spleen, was provided with a blood transfusion every 20 days to maintain hemoglobin levels between 90 and 100 g/l. Sanger sequencing combined with reverse transcription閳ユ唴uantitative polymerase chain reaction (RT閳ユ唴PCR) and Gap閳ユ厼CR revealed that the proband was a carrier of 4 compound heterozygous mutations: Hemoglobin subunit 灏?(HBB):IVS閳ユ厲I閳?54(C>T)灏?; Southeast Asian閳ユ唸ype閳ユ吋ereditary persistence of fetal hemoglobin (SEA閳ユ厰PFH); HBB:c316閳?48G>T; hemoglobin subunit 浼? (HBA2):c.46G>A. The father of the proband was identified as a carrier of the heterozygous SEA閳ユ厰PFH mutation, the mother was a carrier of compound heterozygous mutations of HBB:IVS閳ユ厲I閳?54(C>T) and HBA2:c.46G>A, and the elder sister was heterozygous for HBB:IVS閳ユ厲I閳?54(C>T)灏?. Based on these genetic results, it was determined that the proband had both of heavy 灏鹃垾鎲坔alassemia and 浼垾鎲坔alassemia. Upon human leukocyte antigen matching, bone marrow transplantation (BMT) was successfully performed on the proband by selecting his HLA閳ユ叾ompatible sister as a donor. Following treatment, the proband was revealed to only carry the IVS閳ユ厲I閳?54(C>T)灏? heterozygous mutation, and further regular blood transfusions have been avoided; BMT results remained normal at six months follow閳ユ唹p.
