Title: Sciatic neurostenalgia: caused by total hip arthroplasty, cured by late neurolysis.
Abstract: We describe a patient with a painful sciatic neuropathy after total hip arthroplasty. Treatment was confined to neuroleptic and analgesic agents until neurolysis at seven years abolished pain and restored function.
